noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 The condition 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{\perp}\left(q_{s}\right)G\left(q_{s}\right)\ne0$
\end_inset

 in Theorem~
\backslash
ref{thm:singularity-necessity} implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $Ndh\left(q_{s}\right)G\left(q_{s}\right)\ne0$
\end_inset

.
 Consequently,
 equation~(
\backslash
ref{eq:condition-for-dq}) either admits two solutions of opposite signs or has no solution at all.
 The former case permits the existence of smooth trajectories 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{*}\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

,
 as demonstrated in section above,
 but destroys the structure of the controlled invariant manifold.
 Therefore,
 Definition~
\backslash
ref{def:VHC} excludes from consideration all trajectories described in Theorem~
\backslash
ref{thm:singularity-necessity}.
